The second constraint is the cycle of capital expenditure. The technology industry requires massive capital investment. Data centers, chip manufacturing, and fiber optic network R&D all require significant investment. When everyone is investing, overcapacity occurs, leading to a price crash. The semiconductor industry is a prime

